Cornelia was the daughter of Cornelius Scipio, a man of consular rank, and Scribonia, the sister of L. Scribonius Libo, and afterwards the wife of Augustus. P. Cornelius Scipio, conanime. 16, was her brother. Her husband Paullus Aemilius Lepidus, a nephew of the triumvir of that name, was an officer in the Republican army. but afterwards joined Octavian, was consul rac. 34, and censor nc. 22. Their children were L. Aemilius Paullus, consul aa). r, aasentias Lepidus consulas). 6, and Aemilia Lepida, of whom nothing is known.
